The only problem I have with them is that they last (my first pair went through 3 music festivals, various concerts, New York City and Germany), but after a while they just get gross, and if it rains forget it. I tried water proofing them, but I do realize they are canvas so may not be as durable as leather shoes. I also wish it was easier to clean/wash them. My first pair I tried to wash (I followed the instructions that are online very carefully) and the inside sole shrunk and got all weird, so it was really uncomfortable to wear them. With that said these are issues that you have to kind of accept when purchasing canvas shoes, so overall these are great.Tip for first time purchasers of Toms: the only way to break them in is to BREAK THEM IN. The first time I purchased a pair I wore them around the house for weeks trying to break them in and they just wouldnt stretch out enough.
